// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// CHANGELOG v9.9.0 — Context Intelligence Engine Integration
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Integrates GodTier_ContextEngine v1.4.0 as the arbiter layer above all signals.
// Every render/alert decision is now context-qualified before firing.
//
// [1] CIE IMPORT — GodTier_ContextEngine/7 imported as ctx_eng.
//     analyze_context() called unconditionally every bar (post all signal
//     computations, pre dashboard render) so cie_state is never na when
//     gate wrappers are evaluated. Gate calls use method syntax (v1.3):
//     cie_state.gate_fvg() / .gate_vp_level() / .gate_structure_break() /
//     .gate_ma_cross() / .gate_sweep_reversal()
//
// [2] IFVG FLIP DETECTION — var ifvg_flip_bull / ifvg_flip_bear detect new
//     IFVG spawns each confirmed bar (array size delta + .bias check).
//     Feeds L4 Liquidity layer in analyze_context(). spawn_ifvg() uses
//     array.unshift() so newest IFVG is always at index 0.
//
// [3] SIGNAL GATING — five signal classes now context-qualified:
//     FVG labels:         cie_state.gate_fvg()
//     BOS/CHoCH labels:   cie_state.gate_structure_break()
//     ZZ Sweep labels:    cie_state.gate_sweep_reversal()
//     MA cross bg:        cie_state.gate_ma_cross()
//     VP level alerts:    cie_state.gate_vp_level()
//     Pattern is:  if <signal> and (na(cie_state) or cie_state.<gate>())
//     na() fallback ensures all signals fire ungated before CIE warms up.
//
// [4] DASHBOARD — 11 CIE rows appended after the v9.8 debug section:
//     "── CIE v1.4 ──" separator, Signal Gate, Phase, Score, Bias,
//     L1 Struct, L2 VP, L3 OF, L4 Liq, L5 Mom, Driver, + CONFLICT row.
//     Gated behind show_market_state (reuses existing toggle).
//
// [5] ALERTS — 4 new CIE alert conditions after existing PART 7 alerts:
//     CIE High Conviction Bull / Bear, CIE Gate CLOSED, CIE Layer Conflict.
//
// [6] ma_partial_align TRI-STATE (v1.3 BREAKING FIX) — CIE analyze_context()
//     requires int (1/-1/0), not bool. Derived inline at call site:
//     not na(ma_fast) and not na(ma_medium)
//         ? (ma_fast > ma_medium ? 1 : ma_fast < ma_medium ? -1 : 0) : 0
//     All three branches reachable. Prior bool would have permanently
//     locked L5 Momentum into a two-state calculation.
//
// [7] stacked_imb_count — single-assignment from existing stacked_count local
//     (already computed in the OrderFlow section). No second map traversal.
//
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// CHANGELOG v9.8.1 — VA Cloud Tile Visibility Fix (Cross-Timeframe)
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// 🛠  BUG — Tiles show consistently on 1m but rarely/inconsistently on 5m,
//           15m, 1h — sometimes only the most recent tile or single live tile.
//           Four compounding root causes identified and fixed:
//
// [1] FIX — Neutral state transparency: 75% → 55% (more opaque).
//           color.orange at 75% transp renders near-invisible on dark themes.
//           Neutral state is early-session only (before VA is measured) so
//           making those first tiles more visible is safe and intentional.
//
// [2] FIX — Neutral base color: color.orange → rgb(180,140,60).
//           color.orange has low saturation at high transparency. The amber
//           rgb holds visual weight at 55-75% transparency on all themes.
//
// [3] FIX — TF-aware minimum spawn interval floor added.
//           Old: math.max(1, ...) — interval stays 1 the entire session on
//           higher TFs (sessions have <100 confirmed bars), so the ring buffer
//           fills and churns immediately, discarding all but the newest tiles.
//           New: tf_min_interval: 1m→1, 5m→2, 15m→3, 1h→5, 4h+→8.
//           Distributes tiles evenly across the session instead of front-loading.
//
// [4] FIX — Fallback spawn when tile array is empty after session_age > 0.
//           With the new tf_min_interval floor (e.g. 5 on 1h), no historical
//           tile fires until bar 5. If the live tile is invisible during that
//           gap (Neutral state), nothing shows at all. Fallback forces one
//           spawn on the first confirmed bar after open.
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// CHANGELOG v9.8.0 — Full Dynamic Scaling Pass (Every Parameter Anchored)
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// After this version every parameter in the system has a physical anchor:
// a time-equivalent bar count, ATR-relative price distance, or volume-relative
// delta. The indicator now behaves identically across 1m, 5m, 15m, and 1h
// without any manual tuning between timeframes.
//
// [A] Failed Auction lookback — target ~40 min equivalent
//     1m→40 bars  5m→8 bars  15m→3 bars  1h→2 bars (floor)
//     Input: fa_lookback_auto (default ON). Raw 8-bar window was 8 minutes
//     on 1m (noise floor) and 8 hours on 1h (not a breakout, just structure).
//
// [B] SMD lookback — target ~50 min equivalent
//     1m→50  5m→10  15m→3  1h→2 (floor). Input: smd_lookback_auto (ON).
//
// [C] FVG extend bars — target ~100 min forward projection
//     1m→100  5m→20  15m→7  1h→2. Input: fvg_extend_auto (ON).
//     FVG boxes now represent the same forward time window on every TF.
//
// [D] MA momentum lookbacks — target ~25 min (fast) and ~50 min (medium)
//     MOST IMPACTFUL: f_momentum(ma_fast, 5) on 1m = 5-minute MA slope.
//     That's effectively instantaneous — the dynamic color was pure noise.
//     On 1h, 5 bars = 5-hour slope — too slow to be actionable.
//     Now: 1m→25/50 bars  5m→5/10  15m→2/3  1h→1/1 (floor 1).
//     The momentum color on every MA line now describes the same ~25/50 min
//     institutional window regardless of which TF you're on.
//
// [E] Bubble proximity — ATR × 0.12 replaces mintick × ticks
//     mintick × N is instrument-specific (NQ=0.25, BTC=0.5, ES=0.25).
//     ATR-relative keeps the "near key level" band proportional to volatility.
//
// [F] POC drift display threshold — ATR × 0.04 replaces mintick × 5
//     Red threshold raised to ATR × 0.15 (was mintick × 20).
//
// [G] Bubble min delta — 5% of avg bar delta replaces raw 50-contract floor
//     Raw 50 killed bubble generation on thin sessions and was too permissive
//     on heavy institutional flow. Volume-relative keeps density stable.
//
// Dashboard: new debug rows for eff_fa_lookback, eff_smd_lookback,
//            eff_fvg_extend, eff_fast_mom_len, eff_medium_mom_len.
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// CHANGELOG v9.7.0 — Label System Overhaul + Signal Quality Fixes
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// 🛠  BUG — Labels stop generating after ~100 bars (critical):
//             Root cause: array.pop() in all pruning while-loops was deleting
//             the NEWEST label (from array end) on every bar after cap was hit.
//             push() adds to end → pop() removes from end = every new label
//             instantly deleted. First 100 labels frozen forever.
//             FIX: All pruning loops changed array.pop() → array.shift()
//             (shift removes from front = oldest first = correct FIFO pruning).
//             Affected arrays: pattern_labels (×8 calls), ms_hhll_labels (×2),
//             ms_bos_labels (×2), ms_hist_res/sup_lines/labels (×8).
//             Also removes misleading comment "use pop instead of shift to avoid
//             bounds errors" — that comment was incorrect. shift() is safe here
//             because the while-size-guard prevents calling shift on empty array.
//
// 🏷️  LABEL SYSTEM — Tier-based visibility controls:
//             New group "🏷️ Label Visibility" with toggles per signal tier.
//             Tier 1 (always on): SWEEP+FA, CHoCH, FAIL BULL/BEAR, ZZ SWEEP.
//             Tier 2 (on by default): HH/HL/LH/LL, BOS.
//             Tier 3 (off by default, dashboard-only): ABS, EXHAUST, ICE, DIV,
//             DIST/ACCUM — these fire too frequently on NQ scalping timeframes
//             to be useful as chart labels; moved to dashboard signal rows.
//
// 📉  LABEL CAPS REDUCED — prevents chart clutter:
//             pattern_labels: 100 → 30
//             ms_hhll_labels: 60  → 20
//             ms_bos_labels:  40  → 20
//
// 🎨  VISUAL HIERARCHY — label size differentiation by priority:
//             Tier 1 (SWEEP+FA, CHoCH, FAIL): size.normal (unchanged, correct)
//             Tier 2 HH/HL/LH/LL: size.tiny + label.style_none (text-only,
//             no filled box background — reduces visual noise on busy charts)
//             BOS: size.small (unchanged)
//
// 🔊  SIGNAL QUALITY — SMD price move filter added:
//             f_smart_money_div() now requires math.abs(close - close[lookback])
//             >= ta.atr(14) * 0.75 before firing distribution or accumulation.
//             Without this gate the signal fires on every NQ pullback/chop.
//             ATR * 0.75 ensures price actually moved before classifying intent.
//
// 🔊  SIGNAL QUALITY — Absorption threshold raised:
//             Inline volume gate added: volume must exceed ta.sma(volume,20)*2.5
//             before detectAbsorption() is called. The library default of 1.5×
//             fires constantly on NQ open and news events. 2.5× reduces noise
//             while preserving genuine high-volume absorption detection.
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// CHANGELOG v9.6.0 — Ghost Cloud Tile Fix (Box Budget + Phantom Boxes)
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// 🛠  BUG — Ghost cloud tiles still not visible after v9.5.1 patch:
//             Root cause 1: max_boxes_count=750 was still insufficient.
//             Worst-case at barstate.islast: Mode 2 profile (200×2=400 boxes)
//             + heatmap overlay (200) + LVN (200) + fast lanes (~50) +
//             imbalances (~50) + FVG/IFVG split-boxes (~80) = ~980 boxes.
//             Pine evicts OLDEST first — always active_va_cloud — making the
//             ghost cloud/tiles invisible.
//             Root cause 2: LVN / fast_lane / imbalance arrays accumulated
//             across the session with no per-bar cap, so even with the FVG prune
//             at the top of barstate.islast, those 3 arrays alone could hold
//             hundreds of stale boxes before cleanup.
//             Root cause 3: active_va_cloud := na was set TWICE on session
//             boundary (once in zoneEnd, once in newSession) — the second reset
//             wiped va_cloud_left timing, anchoring the cloud at wrong bar.
//             Root cause 4: color.silver at base_transp 75-96 renders
//             near-white on dark themes, invisible on light themes.
//
//   FIX 1:   max_boxes_count raised 750 → 1000.
//   FIX 2:   Hard caps added before barstate.islast render:
//             lvn_boxes > 50, fast_lane_boxes > 40, imbalance_zones > 40.
//   FIX 3:   Removed duplicate active_va_cloud := na from newSession block.
//             zoneEnd already handles delete + nil. Duplicate corrupted
//             va_cloud_left anchor for new session's cloud left edge.
//   FIX 4:   color.silver → color.rgb(140,160,200) for "Stable" va_state.
//             Blue-grey holds visual weight at high transparency on all themes.
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// CHANGELOG v9.5.1 — VA Ghost Cloud Restoration
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// 🛠  BUG — Developing VA Ghost Cloud not rendering after v9.5.0 patch:
//             Root cause: FVG/IFVG split-box rendering (2 boxes per gap × up to
//             20 active FVGs + 20 IFVGs = up to 80 boxes) pushed total box budget
//             past max_boxes_count=500 mid-session. Pine silently evicted the
//             oldest boxes first — active_va_cloud — leaving no cloud visible.
//             Additionally, the "Neutral" va_state fallback color was color.teal
//             which at base_transp 75-96 renders near-invisible on dark backgrounds.
//
//   FIX 1:   max_boxes_count raised 500 → 750 in indicator() declaration.
//   FIX 2:   fvg_lib.prune() moved to TOP of barstate.islast block so FVG
//             boxes are capped BEFORE profile render adds ~200 new boxes.
//             Removed duplicate call from bottom of the same block.
//   FIX 3:   "Neutral" va_state color changed color.teal → color.orange.
//             Self-healing — cloud is always visible regardless of va_state.
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// 🛠  BUG 1 — VA Ghost Cloud disappearing / rendering white (CRITICAL):
//             Root cause: The tile-array approach (va_cloud_boxes) spawned one
//             box every 5 bars and kept up to 400 tiles. At barstate.islast,
//             profile heatmap boxes (200) + FVG boxes (40) + LVN/FastLane/
//             Imbalance boxes + the 400 cloud tiles routinely exceeded Pine's
//             max_boxes_count=500 hard limit. Pine silently deleted the OLDEST
//             boxes first — the cloud tiles — leaving only the invisible shell
//             (bgcolor=white,100 = fully transparent). Cloud appeared absent or
//             "filled white with no context / color coding."
//             FIX: Replaced the entire va_cloud_boxes tile system with a single
//             updating box (active_va_cloud). Box budget at barstate.islast
//             drops from ~680 to ~283 — well under limit. Color now updates
//             every tick (not every 5 bars) so delta-tint and VA state tracking
//             are tighter. va_cloud_boxes var array, opt.batch_prune_drawings
//             call, and tile spawn/update loops all removed.
//
// 🛠  BUG 2 — Session label appearing at session start, missing near live bar:
//             Root cause: center_x formula placed label at 85% of elapsed
//             session length. Early in a session this was near bar 0. On a full
//             day viewed at the live bar, the label sat hundreds of bars to the
//             left of the viewport. FIX: label_x = bar_index + 3, so the
//             session summary label always tracks the live bar's right edge.
//
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// CHANGELOG v9.2 — Elite MA Intelligence Integration
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// ➕ [1] ZZ STRUCTURAL SWEEP LAYER
//        Imports EliteMA_ATRZigZag/4. Calls getZigZagLevels() every bar to
//        maintain confirmed ATR-adaptive swing highs/lows. getLiquiditySweep()
//        fires when price breaches a confirmed swing level then aggressively
//        rejects back through it. High-conviction tier fires when ZZ sweep AND
//        session failed auction coincide simultaneously — two independent
//        confirmation frameworks agreeing on the same reversal.
//        Labels: "🎯 ZZ SWEEP" (standalone) / "🎯 SWEEP+FA" (high-conviction).
//        Dashboard: ZZ Bias (structural HH/HL state), ZZ Levels.
//        Alerts: ZZ Bull/Bear Sweep, High-Conv Bull/Bear Sweep+FA.
//
// ➕ [2] DELTA STRENGTH OSCILLATOR
//        Normalized CVD rate-of-change, −100 to +100. Unlike flow_pressure
//        (instantaneous buy-sell ratio snapshot), delta_strength measures
//        whether order flow is ACCELERATING or decelerating — telling you
//        whether a POC hold is likely to continue or roll over before price
//        confirms. Implemented inline (no extra import). Dashboard: row added
//        after CVD with directional arrow (▲/▼/–).
//
// ➕ [3] SMART MONEY DIVERGENCE → IMBALANCE CONFIDENCE FLAG
//        Detects distribution (price rising + volume declining) and
//        accumulation (price falling + volume declining). When stacked
//        imbalances are active, SMD flags zones being sold-into or loaded-up-at
//        before price has moved, adding a "📤 DIST" / "📥 ACCUM" warning label.
//        Wired into market state priority. Resets on session.
//
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// CHANGELOG v9.1
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// ✂️  REMOVED: Entire GodTier_TradeSetups system (6 setups, management loop,
//              Kelly sizing, Fibonacci TP/SL, trade visuals, history table,
//              smart setup selection, MA alignment gate, position tracking).
//              All core mechanics are fully intact.
// ✂️  REMOVED: GodTier_TradeSetups import — library no longer loaded.
// ✂️  REMOVED: Trade-only inputs: group_setups, group_viz, group_fib.
// ✂️  REMOVED: Dead code: ZoneTracker type, active_zone_trackers array.
//
// 🔱 ENHANCED: VA Ghost Cloud
//   - Prior session VAH/VAL drawn as persistent dotted reference zone extending
//     forward from each session boundary.
//   - Delta-tinted cloud: blends base state color toward bull/bear based on
//     cumulative flow pressure.
//   - VA width transparency: fatter VA = more opaque cloud.
//   - VA reclaim/rejection border: lime on reclaim, red on rejection.
//
// 🔱 ENHANCED: Fast Lanes — Merged Zone Rendering
//   - Single renderMergedFastLanes pass replaces dual renderSinglePrints calls.
//   - Adjacent qualifying bins merged into contiguous zone boxes.
//   - fast_lane_min_stack input suppresses single-bin noise.
//   - Fill-check: zones price is currently inside are skipped.
//   - Single box array, single cleanup.
//
// 🛠  PATCHED (post-v9.1 audit):
//   BUG 1 — f_ma_calculate: removed orphaned `float result = na` variable.
//            Switch is now an expression — all 8 MA types return correctly.
//            Previously every MA call returned `na` silently.
//   BUG 2 — f_ma_calculate: option strings "Hull MA"/"ZeroLag EMA" renamed to
//            "HMA"/"ZLEMA" to match input.string dropdown. Previously those
//            two branches never executed.
//   BUG 3 — int() cast replaced with math.round() in two places.
//            int() is not a Pine v6 function; caused compile errors.
//   BUG 4 — alertcondition exhaustion: {{exhaustion_type}} is not a valid
//            Pine placeholder. Split into two typed alertconditions.
//   BUG 5 — Prior VA box extension moved outside bar_index % 5 gate.
//            Now runs every bar (not only on 5th bars), guarded against
//            session-change bars to avoid cap/extend race.
//   BUG 6 — border_col defaulted to color.new(color.white, 100) instead of
//            bare `na` for Pine v6 color-type strictness.
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

strategy("God Tier VP - v9.9.6 Strategy Harness", shorttitle="GT_VP_v9.9.6_STRAT",
     overlay=true, pyramiding=0, initial_capital=50000,
     default_qty_type=strategy.percent_of_equity, default_qty_value=10,
     max_lines_count=500, max_boxes_count=500, max_labels_count=500,
     max_polylines_count=100, max_bars_back=5000)
// AUDIT FIX: TradingView hard-limits box/line/label IDs at 500.
// Rendering now uses a conservative profile row budget below so profile bars,
// heatmap, FVG/IFVG zones, VA cloud, LVN, fast lanes, and imbalances can coexist
// under the legal 500-box ceiling.

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------
// LIBRARY IMPORTS
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------
import iruntvmgmt/GodTier_Binning/4      as binning
import iruntvmgmt/GodTierEngine/14       as gte
import iruntvmgmt/GodTier_OrderFlow/4    as of
import iruntvmgmt/GodTier_Optimization/6 as opt
import iruntvmgmt/GodTier_Rendering/8    as render   // v8: renderMergedFastLanes + current safety fixes
import iruntvmgmt/GodTier_Bubbles/3      as bubbles
import iruntvmgmt/GodTier_Controller/9   as ctrl
import iruntvmgmt/MA_Library/4           as ma_lib
import iruntvmgmt/EliteMA_ATRZigZag/4    as zz       // v4: paired structure bias + professional liquidity sweeps
import iruntvmgmt/GodTier_FVG/2          as fvg_lib  // v2: FVG + IFVG engine (semantic v1.1)
import iruntvmgmt/GodTier_ContextEngine/7 as ctx_eng  // v7: context intelligence arbiter (semantic v1.4.1)

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------
// STRATEGY HARNESS INPUTS
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------
group_strategy = "Strategy Harness"
enable_strategy = input.bool(false, "Enable Strategy Orders", group=group_strategy,
    tooltip="OFF keeps this script visually safe while still compiling as a strategy. ON routes the typed v9.9.6 signals into strategy orders.")
strategy_mode = input.string("All Signals", "Trade Signal Mode",
    options=["All Signals", "Reversal Only", "Rotation Only", "Structure Only"], group=group_strategy,
    tooltip="Reversal = Sweep+FA and Failed Auction. Rotation = POC reclaim/rejection inside value. Structure = CHoCH/BOS/trend continuation.")
strategy_strictness = input.string("Normal", "Entry Strictness",
    options=["Loose", "Normal", "Strict"], group=group_strategy,
    tooltip="Loose = trigger plus CIE gate not closed. Normal = trigger plus signal-specific CIE gate and directional flow. Strict = Normal plus stronger CIE alignment.")
allow_strategy_longs = input.bool(true, "Allow Longs", group=group_strategy)
allow_strategy_shorts = input.bool(true, "Allow Shorts", group=group_strategy)
strategy_rr = input.float(1.5, "Fallback R:R Target", minval=0.5, maxval=5.0, step=0.25, group=group_strategy,
    tooltip="Used when the profile target is missing or too close to the entry.")
strategy_atr_stop_mult = input.float(1.0, "ATR Stop Multiplier", minval=0.25, maxval=5.0, step=0.25, group=group_strategy)
strategy_level_buffer_atr = input.float(0.10, "Level Buffer ATR", minval=0.0, maxval=1.0, step=0.01, group=group_strategy,
    tooltip="Small ATR buffer beyond POC/VA/swing levels for strategy stops.")
strategy_timeout_bars = input.int(30, "Timeout Bars", minval=0, maxval=300, group=group_strategy,
    tooltip="Closes open strategy trades after this many bars. 0 disables timeouts.")

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------
// 🎯 TRIPLE MA SYSTEM INPUTS
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------
group_ma = "🎯 Triple MA Trend Filter"
ma_auto_lengths = input.bool(true, "Auto-Scale MA Lengths (TF-Aware)", group=group_ma,
    tooltip="ON: lengths preserve the base-timeframe duration across chart timeframes. With a 5m base, 9/21/50 becomes 45/105/250 on 1m and 3/7/17 on 15m. OFF: use manual lengths unchanged.")
ma_base_tf = input.timeframe("5", "MA Base Timeframe", group=group_ma,
    tooltip="Reference timeframe for dynamic MA scaling. Lengths are interpreted as this timeframe's bars, then translated to the current chart timeframe.")
ma_adaptive_vol = input.bool(false, "Volatility-Adaptive MA Lengths", group=group_ma,
    tooltip="Blends short/long MA endpoints by ATR percentile. Quiet markets smooth out; volatile markets react faster.")
ma_vol_sensitivity = input.float(25.0, "MA Volatility Sensitivity", minval=0.0, maxval=50.0, step=5.0, group=group_ma,
    tooltip="Maximum percentage shift used by volatility-adaptive endpoints.")
ma_adaptive_type = input.bool(false, "Regime-Adaptive MA Type", group=group_ma,
    tooltip="Uses the prior bar's regime to select the MA family: volatile=Hull, compressed=WMA, trending=EMA, ranging=SMA.")
enable_ma_system    = input.bool(true, "Enable MA System", group=group_ma,
    tooltip="Master toggle for the triple MA trend filter system. Core logic for the L5 Momentum CIE layer.")
ma_filter_mode      = input.string("Off", "MA Filter Mode",
    options=["Off", "2-MA (Fast/Medium)", "3-MA (All Aligned)"],
    tooltip="Off: No filtering | 2-MA: Fast vs Medium | 3-MA: Full alignment", group=group_ma)
ma_filter_strict    = input.bool(false, "Strict Mode (Price Position)",
    tooltip="Require price above/below Fast MA for long/short", group=group_ma)

ma_fast_length      = input.int(9,  "Fast MA Length",   minval=1, group=group_ma,
    tooltip="Primary momentum anchor. Fast reaction to price changes.")
ma_medium_length    = input.int(21, "Medium MA Length", minval=1, group=group_ma,
    tooltip="Standard trend anchor. Used for 2-MA cross and cloud core.")
ma_slow_length      = input.int(50, "Slow MA Length",   minval=1, group=group_ma,
    tooltip="Long-term trend anchor. Defines the outer boundary for 3-MA alignment.")

ma_type             = input.string("EMA", "MA Type",
    options=["SMA", "EMA", "WMA", "VWMA", "HMA", "DEMA", "TEMA", "ZLEMA", "Smooth SMA", "Triangular MA", "SuperSmooth MA", "T3"], group=group_ma,
    tooltip="Calculates all 3 MAs using this variant. EMA/VWMA recommended for institutional flow.")

show_ma_visual      = input.bool(true,  "Show MA Lines",          group=group_ma,
    tooltip="Toggle visibility of the Fast, Medium, and Slow MA lines.")
show_ma_cloud       = input.bool(true,  "Show MA Cloud",          group=group_ma,
    tooltip="Draws a shaded cloud between Fast and Medium MAs. Fills on full alignment.")
show_trend_bg       = input.bool(false, "Show Trend Background",  group=group_ma,
    tooltip="Colors the entire chart background based on high-conviction 3-MA trend alignment.")

// MA colors are momentum-driven (Elite MA aesthetic) — no manual color inputs needed.
// Fast/Mid: 3-tier dynamic color (strong/medium/weak) keyed to momentum strength.
// Slow: white when rising, gray(40) when falling.
// Cloud: green(90) on full bull align, red(90) on full bear align.

c_bg_strong_bull    = input.color(color.new(color.green, 97),  "Strong Bull BG", inline="bg1",   group=group_ma)
c_bg_weak_bull      = input.color(color.new(color.green, 99),  "Weak Bull",      inline="bg1",   group=group_ma)
c_bg_strong_bear    = input.color(color.new(color.red, 97),    "Strong Bear BG", inline="bg2",   group=group_ma)
c_bg_weak_bear      = input.color(color.new(color.red, 99),    "Weak Bear",      inline="bg2",   group=group_ma)

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------
// SESSION & EXECUTION INPUTS
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------
group_session    = "Session Configuration"
sessionType      = input.string('Daily', 'Session Type',
    options=['Tokyo','London','New York','Daily','Weekly','Monthly','Quarterly','Yearly'],
    group=group_session)
showCur          = input.bool(true, 'Show Live Session', group=group_session)

group_execution  = "Real-Time Execution"
realtime_execution  = input.bool(true,  "Real-Time Execution (Live Ticks)", group=group_execution,
    tooltip="Calculates profile on every tick. Disable for performance on low-end devices.")
confirm_on_close    = input.bool(false, "Require Bar Close (Safety Mode)",  group=group_execution,
    tooltip="Wait for the bar to close before finalized signals. Prevents flickering/repainting.")
min_tick_spacing    = input.int(5,      "Min Ticks Between Checks", minval=1, maxval=50, group=group_execution,
    tooltip="Minimum price move (in ticks) required before recalculating the live profile. Saves CPU.")

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------
// BINNING & COMPRESSION INPUTS
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------
group_bins = "Dynamic Binning System"
use_dynamic_bins            = input.bool(true,    "ATR-Based Dynamic Bins",    group=group_bins,
    tooltip="Calculate bin size dynamically based on session volatility. Keeps profile detail balanced.")
granularity_factor          = input.int(40,       "Granularity Factor",        minval=10, maxval=100, group=group_bins,
    tooltip="Controls bin density. Higher = more detailed profile (expensive), Lower = smoother (fast).")
granularity_auto = input.bool(true, "Auto-Scale Granularity (TF-Aware)", group=group_bins,
    tooltip="ON: adjusts the ATR bin-count base per timeframe. Your fixed value is the 5m baseline. 1m→×1.4 (finer), 15m→×0.75, 1h→×0.55, 4h→×0.35. Prevents over-binning on 1m and flat profiles on 4h. OFF: use fixed value above.")
fixed_bins                  = input.int(50,       "Fixed Bins (if dynamic off)", minval=10, maxval=200, group=group_bins,
    tooltip="Number of horizontal rows if Dynamic Bins is OFF.")
enable_adaptive_granularity = input.bool(true,    "Adaptive Granularity",      group=group_bins,
    tooltip="Refines bin size as the session expands. Crucial for long-running daily/weekly sessions.")

compression_mode            = input.string("Hybrid", "Compression Mode",
    options=["Off","Threshold-Only","Time-Only","Hybrid"], group=group_bins,
    tooltip="Method for bin merging to save memory. Hybrid combines time and size triggers.")
compression_factor          = input.int(2,       "Compression Factor",         minval=2, maxval=5,   group=group_bins,
    tooltip="Ratio of bins to merge (e.g. 2:1). Higher = more aggressive memory optimization.")
compression_trigger_size    = input.int(40000,   "Primary Threshold",          minval=10000, maxval=100000, step=5000, group=group_bins,
    tooltip="Maximum allowed map size before compression is triggered. 40k is stable for NQ.")
compression_trigger_auto = input.bool(true, "Auto-Scale Compression Trigger (TF-Aware)", group=group_bins,
    tooltip="ON: scales the map-size threshold that triggers compression. Lower TFs accumulate bins faster — trigger fires earlier. 1m→×0.2 (8k), 5m→×1 (40k base), 15m→×3 (80k cap), 1h+→80k cap. OFF: use fixed threshold above.")
enable_multi_stage          = input.bool(true,   "Multi-Stage Compression",    group=group_bins,
    tooltip="Allow multiple rounds of compression for extremely large sessions (e.g. Weekly/Monthly).")
time_compression_bars       = input.int(2000,    "Time Trigger (bars)",        minval=500, maxval=5000, step=100, group=group_bins,
    tooltip="Session age (in bars) before automatic time-based compression occurs.")

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------
// VISUALIZATION INPUTS
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------
group_vis = "Visualization Engine"
profile_width_pct       = input.float(0.3,   "Profile Width (% of session)", minval=0.1, maxval=0.9, step=0.05, group=group_vis,
    tooltip="Horizontal space allocated to the profile. 0.3 = 30% of session box width.")
use_heatmap             = input.bool(true,   "Gradient Heatmap",            group=group_vis,
    tooltip="Color volume bins based on intensity. Higher volume = warmer colors.")
use_enhanced_heatmap    = input.bool(true,   "Enhanced Thermal Tiers",      group=group_vis,
    tooltip="Uses refined color tiers to distinguish LVN/HVN/POC regions for faster visual processing.")
use_polyline            = input.bool(true,   "Polyline Rendering (Organic Mode)", group=group_vis,
    tooltip="Draws a connecting line through the volume profile shell for improved readability.")
smooth_polyline         = input.bool(true,   "Smooth Polyline (3-Bin MA)",   group=group_vis,
    tooltip="Applies a 3-bin moving average to the polyline for a cleaner, non-jagged profile shape.")
dispMode                = input.string('Mode 2', 'Bar Mode', ['Mode 1','Mode 2','Mode 3'], group=group_vis,
    tooltip="Render style: Mode 1 (Simple), Mode 2 (Standard/Balanced), Mode 3 (Complex/High-Res).")
showSbox                = input.bool(true,   'Show Session Box',             group=group_vis,
    tooltip="Draws the bounding box around the current session.")
showLabels              = input.bool(true,   'Show Session Labels',          group=group_vis,
    tooltip="Displays metadata labels (session type, stats) inside the session box.")
show_profile_shape      = input.bool(true, "Show Profile Shape Analysis", group=group_vis,
    tooltip="Flags D-Shape/P-Shape/b-Shape profiles to identify if market is trending or balanced.")

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------
// VALUE AREA INPUTS
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------
group_va = "Value Area Configuration"
va_percentage           = input.int(70,  "Value Area %",            minval=50, maxval=95, group=group_va,
    tooltip="Institutional Fair Value. Typical setting 70%. Defines the high-volume core of the profile.")
showPoc                 = input.bool(true,  "Show POC",              group=group_va,
    tooltip="Toggle visibility of the Point of Control — the single price level with highest volume.")
showVA                  = input.bool(true,  "Show VAH/VAL Lines",    group=group_va,
    tooltip="Toggle visibility of the Value Area High (VAH) and Value Area Low (VAL) lines.")
showVAb                 = input.bool(false, "Show Value Area Box",   group=group_va,
    tooltip="Renders a shaded rectangle covering the entire Value Area range.")
show_va_metrics         = input.bool(true,  "VA Breathing Metrics",  group=group_va,
    tooltip="Displays status updates like 'Expanding' or 'Contracting' in the session summary.")
va_expansion_threshold  = input.float(1.1, "Expansion Threshold",   minval=1.05, maxval=1.5,  group=group_va,
    tooltip="Multiplier for VA width to qualify as 'Expanding' (e.g. 1.1 = 10% wider than average).")
va_contraction_threshold= input.float(0.9, "Contraction Threshold", minval=0.5,  maxval=0.95, group=group_va,
    tooltip="Multiplier for VA width to qualify as 'Contracting' (e.g. 0.9 = 10% narrower than average).")
va_breath_auto = input.bool(true, "Auto-Scale VA Breathing Thresholds", group=group_va,
    tooltip="ON: widens Expand/Contract bands proportionally when session volatility is elevated (ATR > 50-bar avg). Low-vol sessions keep tight 1.1/0.9. High-vol sessions expand to prevent false 'Expanding' readings on normal chop. OFF: use fixed thresholds above.")

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------
// GOD TIER FEATURES INPUTS
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------
group_god = "God Tier Features"
show_ghost_trails   = input.bool(true,  "POC Ghost Trails (Stepline)",           group=group_god,
    tooltip="Draws a stepline following the migration of the POC across the session. Visualizes momentum.")
use_colored_ghost   = input.bool(true,  "Colored Ghost Trails",                   group=group_god,
    tooltip="Tints ghost trails based on directional POC migration (Green = rising, Red = falling).")
ghost_atr_filter    = input.float(0.05,  "Ghost Trail Min ATR Move",   minval=0.01, maxval=1.0, step=0.01, group=group_god,
    tooltip="✅ v9.4.1 FIX: Base multiplier for ghost trail threshold. Timeframe-adaptive scaling applied: 1m/5m (0.3x), 15m (0.5x), 1h-4h (0.7x), daily+ (1.0x). Default 0.05 works across all timeframes.")
show_va_cloud       = input.bool(true,  "Developing VA Cloud",                    group=group_god,
    tooltip="Draws a dynamic background cloud that represents the developing Value Area. Updates every tick.")

// v9.1: Enhanced VA Cloud controls
show_prior_va           = input.bool(true,  "Prior Session VA Reference",           group=group_god,
    tooltip="Draw prior session's Value Area as a persistent dotted zone extending forward.")
va_cloud_delta_tint     = input.bool(true,  "Delta-Tinted Cloud",                   group=group_god,
    tooltip="Blend cloud color toward bull/bear based on flow pressure. Distinguishes expanding-with-buyers from expanding-against-buyers.")
show_va_reclaim_border  = input.bool(true,  "VA Reclaim/Rejection Border",          group=group_god,
    tooltip="Lime border when price reclaims inside VA. Red border when price rejects and exits.")

show_stacked_imb    = input.bool(true,  "Stacked Imbalances",                     group=group_god,
    tooltip="Highlights prices where institutional buyers or sellers significantly overpowered the other side.")
show_lvn_marks      = input.bool(true,  "LVN Markers",                            group=group_god,
    tooltip="Draws markers at Low Volume Nodes (LVNs) — prices where institutional flow was most efficient/ignored.")
show_fast_lanes     = input.bool(true,  "Fast Lanes (Liquidity Voids)",           group=group_god,
    tooltip="Highlights contiguous price gaps with extremely low volume. Acts as 'slippery' zones for fast price moves.")
show_bubbles        = input.bool(true,  "Footprint Bubbles (Point of Truth)",     group=group_god,
    tooltip="Renders circles at prices with high-volume order flow signatures (Absorptions, Icebergs, etc.).")

lvn_threshold       = input.float(0.15, "LVN Threshold",                  minval=0.05, maxval=0.3,  group=group_god)
fast_lane_threshold = input.float(0.15, "Fast Lane Threshold (vs max vol)",minval=0.05, maxval=0.5, step=0.05, group=group_god,
    tooltip="Bins below this fraction of max volume qualify as Fast Lane. Lower = stricter (only true voids). Replaces the old 0.30/0.05 dual threshold.")
fast_lane_min_stack = input.int(2,      "Fast Lane Min Zone Width (bins)", minval=1, maxval=10, group=group_god,
    tooltip="Minimum consecutive qualifying bins to draw a zone. Suppresses single-bin noise. 2–3 recommended.")
void_thresh_auto = input.bool(true, "Auto-Scale LVN & Fast Lane Thresholds", group=group_god,
    tooltip="ON: scales LVN and Fast Lane void thresholds with session bar count. Short sessions (1m) have lower max_volume baselines — threshold raises to compensate and keep void detection consistent. OFF: use fixed values above.")
imbalance_ratio     = input.float(3.0,  "Imbalance Threshold",            minval=1.5, maxval=5.0, group=group_god)
imbalance_ratio_auto = input.bool(true, "Auto-Scale Imbalance Ratio (Volatility-Aware)", group=group_god,
    tooltip="ON: multiplies base ratio by current/50-bar ATR ratio. High-vol sessions (BTC spike, news NQ) require a higher buy/sell ratio to qualify as a true imbalance. Prevents NQ-tuned 3.0 from firing as noise on BTC. OFF: use fixed ratio above.")

bubble_vol_threshold    = input.float(2.0,  "Volume Threshold (StdDev)",    minval=-0.5, maxval=5.0, step=0.5, group=group_god,
    tooltip="Minimum volume spike required to generate a bubble. Multiplier for the 50-bar Volume StdDev.")
bubble_min_delta        = input.int(50,     "Minimum Delta to Show",        minval=0,  group=group_god,
    tooltip="Minimum net buy/sell volume required for a bubble. Prevents bubbles on low-volume tick noise.")
bubble_size_mode        = input.string("Dynamic", "Size Mode",
    options=["Fixed","Dynamic","Volume-Weighted"], group=group_god,
    tooltip="Fixed: all bubbles same size | Dynamic: scale with volume | Vol-Weighted: scale with delta %.")
bubble_show_ratio       = input.bool(true,  "Show Buy/Sell Ratio",          group=group_god,
    tooltip="Displays the buy/sell ratio text inside the bubble (e.g. 3.5 = buyers are 3.5x stronger).")
max_bubbles             = input.int(50,     "Max Bubbles on Chart",         minval=10, maxval=200, group=group_god,
    tooltip="FIFO cap on number of bubbles. Pruning prevents chart clutter and memory issues.")
bubble_offset           = input.int(3,      "Vertical Offset (ticks)",      minval=0, maxval=20,  group=group_god,
    tooltip="Vertical distance between the price bar and the bubble center (in ticks).")
bubble_color_mode       = input.string("Tiered", "Color Mode",
    options=["Gradient","Vivid","Tiered"], group=group_god,
    tooltip="Tiered: Discrete colors for Low/Mod/Strong. Gradient: Smooth blend. Vivid: High saturation.")
bubble_tier_strength    = input.float(2.0, "Tier Strength Threshold",       minval=1.2, maxval=5.0, group=group_god,
    tooltip="The buy/sell ratio required to reach the 'Strong' (Tier 3) color tier.")
enable_smart_pruning    = input.bool(true,  "Smart Bubble Pruning",         group=group_god,
    tooltip="Dynamically hides older bubbles to maintain chart performance and visual clarity.")
bubble_proximity_ticks  = input.int(10,     "Key Level Proximity (ticks)",  minval=5, maxval=50,   group=group_god,
    tooltip="Distance from POC/VA/SR levels to qualify as a 'Proximity' event in the CIE driver.")
bubble_max_age_bars     = input.int(100,    "Max Bubble Age (bars)",        minval=20, maxval=500, group=group_god,
    tooltip="Lifespan of a bubble in bars before it is automatically deleted.")
bubble_age_auto = input.bool(true, "Auto-Scale Bubble Age (TF-Aware)", group=group_god,
    tooltip="ON: keeps bubble lifespan ~500 min equivalent across TFs. 1m→500 bars, 5m→100 bars (base), 15m→33, 1h→8, 4h→5 (floor). Prevents 4h bubbles from persisting for days. OFF: use fixed bars above.")
bubble_thresh_auto = input.bool(true, "Auto-Scale Bubble Volume Threshold (TF-Aware)", group=group_god,
    tooltip="ON: tightens the StdDev gate on noisy 1m (×1.4) and relaxes it on sparse 4h (×0.55) so bubble density stays consistent across your open charts. OFF: use fixed StdDev above.")
show_bubble_tooltips    = input.bool(true,  "Enhanced Tooltips",            group=group_god)

